12// Common types from OpenGL 1.1

82// GLES 1 types
83// "pub type GLclampx = i32;",
84
85// GLES 1/2 types (tagged for GLES 1)
86// "pub type GLbyte = i8;",
87// "pub type GLubyte = u8;",
88// "pub type GLfloat = GLfloat;",
89// "pub type GLclampf = GLfloat;",
90// "pub type GLfixed = i32;",
91// "pub type GLint64 = i64;",
92// "pub type GLuint64 = u64;",
93// "pub type GLintptr = intptr_t;",
94// "pub type GLsizeiptr = ssize_t;",
95
96// GLES 1/2 types (tagged for GLES 2 - attribute syntax is limited)
97// "pub type GLbyte = i8;",
98// "pub type GLubyte = u8;",
99// "pub type GLfloat = GLfloat;",
100// "pub type GLclampf = GLfloat;",
101// "pub type GLfixed = i32;",
102// "pub type GLint64 = i64;",
103// "pub type GLuint64 = u64;",
104// "pub type GLint64EXT = i64;",
105// "pub type GLuint64EXT = u64;",
106// "pub type GLintptr = intptr_t;",
107// "pub type GLsizeiptr = ssize_t;",
108
109// GLES 2 types (none currently)
110
111// Vendor extension types

113                                                    category: GLenum,
114                                                    severity: GLenum,
115                                                    length: GLsizei,
116                                                    message: *const GLchar,
117                                                    userParam: *mut super::__gl_imports::raw::c_void)>;

119pub type GLvdpauSurfaceNV = GLintptr;

1510
1511        #[allow(dead_code, missing_copy_implementations)]
1512        #[derive(Clone)]
1513        pub struct FnPtr {
1514            /// The function pointer that will be used when calling the function.
1515            f: *const __gl_imports::raw::c_void,
1516            /// True if the pointer points to a real function, false if points to a `panic!` fn.
1517            is_loaded: bool,
1518        }
1519
1520        impl FnPtr {
1521            /// Creates a `FnPtr` from a load attempt.
1522            fn new(ptr: *const __gl_imports::raw::c_void) -> FnPtr {
1523                if ptr.is_null() {
1524                    FnPtr {
1525                        f: missing_fn_panic as *const __gl_imports::raw::c_void,
1526                        is_loaded: false
1527                    }
1528                } else {
1529                    FnPtr { f: ptr, is_loaded: true }
1530                }
1531            }
1532
1533            /// Returns `true` if the function has been successfully loaded.
1534            ///
1535            /// If it returns `false`, calling the corresponding function will fail.
1536            #[inline]
1537            #[allow(dead_code)]
1538            pub fn is_loaded(&self) -> bool {
1539                self.is_loaded
1540            }
1541        }
1542    
1543#[inline(never)]
1544        fn missing_fn_panic() -> ! {
1545            panic!("gl function was not loaded")
1546        }
1547

2676impl Gl {
2677            /// Load each OpenGL symbol using a custom load function. This allows for the
2678            /// use of functions like `glfwGetProcAddress` or `SDL_GL_GetProcAddress`.
2679            ///
2680            /// ~~~ignore
2681            /// let gl = Gl::load_with(|s| glfw.get_proc_address(s));
2682            /// ~~~
2683            #[allow(dead_code, unused_variables)]
2684            pub fn load_with<F>(mut loadfn: F) -> Gl where F: FnMut(&'static str) -> *const __gl_imports::raw::c_void {
2685                #[inline(never)]
2686                fn do_metaloadfn(loadfn: &mut dyn FnMut(&'static str) -> *const __gl_imports::raw::c_void,
2687                                 symbol: &'static str,
2688                                 symbols: &[&'static str])
2689                                 -> *const __gl_imports::raw::c_void {
2690                    let mut ptr = loadfn(symbol);
2691                    if ptr.is_null() {
2692                        for &sym in symbols {
2693                            ptr = loadfn(sym);
2694                            if !ptr.is_null() { break; }
2695                        }
2696                    }
2697                    ptr
2698                }
2699                let mut metaloadfn = |symbol: &'static str, symbols: &[&'static str]| {
2700                    do_metaloadfn(&mut loadfn, symbol, symbols)
2701                };
2702                Gl {
2703Accum: FnPtr::new(metaloadfn("glAccum", &[])),
2704ActiveTexture: FnPtr::new(metaloadfn("glActiveTexture", &["glActiveTextureARB"])),
2705AlphaFunc: FnPtr::new(metaloadfn("glAlphaFunc", &[])),
2706AreTexturesResident: FnPtr::new(metaloadfn("glAreTexturesResident", &[])),
2707ArrayElement: FnPtr::new(metaloadfn("glArrayElement", &["glArrayElementEXT"])),
2708AttachShader: FnPtr::new(metaloadfn("glAttachShader", &["glAttachObjectARB"])),
2709Begin: FnPtr::new(metaloadfn("glBegin", &[])),
2710BeginConditionalRender: FnPtr::new(metaloadfn("glBeginConditionalRender", &["glBeginConditionalRenderNV"])),
2711BeginQuery: FnPtr::new(metaloadfn("glBeginQuery", &["glBeginQueryARB"])),
2712BeginTransformFeedback: FnPtr::new(metaloadfn("glBeginTransformFeedback", &["glBeginTransformFeedbackEXT", "glBeginTransformFeedbackNV"])),
2713BindAttribLocation: FnPtr::new(metaloadfn("glBindAttribLocation", &["glBindAttribLocationARB"])),
